snippet: Prime Minister Sean Chen resigned Friday as popular support for his government plunged and will be replaced by Vice Prime Minister Jiang Yi-hua.
abstract: Taiwan's Prime Min Sean Chen resigns as popular support for his government plunges, and will be replaced by Vice Prime Min Jiang Yi-hua.
lead_paragraph: Prime Minister Sean Chen resigned Friday as popular support for his government plunged and will be replaced by Vice Prime Minister Jiang Yi-hua.

headline.main: Taiwan’s Prime Minister Replaced by His Deputy
headline.print_headline: Taiwan: Prime Minister Replaced by His Deputy
